                )
                
                  2
                
              
            
          
        
        
        
          
            d
          
          
            3
          
        
        k
      
    
    {\displaystyle V(\mathbf {r} )={\frac {-g^{2}}{(2\pi )^{3}}}\int e^{i\mathbf {k\cdot r} }{\frac {4\pi }{k^{2}+(\alpha m)^{2}}}\,\mathrm {d} ^{3}k}
  where the integral is performed over all possible values of the 3-vector momenta k. In this form, and setting the scaling factor to one, 
  
    
      
        α
        =
        1
      
    
    {\displaystyle \alpha =1}
  , the fraction 
  
    
      
        
          
            
              4
              π
            
            
              
                k
                
                  2
                
              
              +
              
