                  2
                
              
            
          
        
      
    
    {\textstyle {\frac {4\pi }{k^{2}+m^{2}}}}
   is seen to be the propagator or Green's function of the Klein–Gordon equation.

Feynman amplitude
The Yukawa potential can be derived as the lowest order amplitude of the interaction of a pair of fermions. The Yukawa interaction couples the fermion field 
  
    
      
        ψ
        (
        x
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle \psi (x)}
   to the meson field 
  
    
      
        ϕ
        (
        x
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle \phi (x)}
   with the coupling term

  
    
      
        
          
            
